			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Nice assessment. My only beef is that the mana efficiency must be higher than even your improved numbers. Why? You forgot the stationary nature of the spell. If the target mob is not cornered or surrounded, push on raids will almost certainly cause a wave to be missed because the target is pushed out of the area of effect. 
<br />

<br />
For small groups push isn't a problem, but agro related ping-ponging is. Many times people in a group accidentally draw agro off the tank causing the mob to run at them. For DoTs or DDs that doesn't matter - they still land for full damage. Rains on the otherhand are completely negated by that potentially reducing the actual damage by 66% (2 of 3 waves avoided). Worse, if the mob runs toward the caster before the spell casting is complete, he/she may end up in area of effect and nuke themselves.
<br />

<br />
I suggest maintaining the current dmg/wave to balance the stationary effect drawback.
<br />

<br />
Aqui<br />_________________<br />Aquilistor Portavendor
<br />
66 Magician
<br />
Ancient Dragon Slayers
<br />
Bertoxxulous
<br />

<br />
Master of the Orb, June 14 2004.
<br />
Blessed by Brell
<br />

